This paper proposes a new approach to topic modeling that focuses on extracting a small number of representative topics for data summarization. This topic modeling approach is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper's emphasis on efficient and simple inference procedures also suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
